# Supabase Branching & CI/CD Reference

Supabase Branching creates an isolated database copy per PR — schema, data, and config.
Requires Pro plan. Prevents running migrations directly against production.

---

## Why Branching Matters

```
Without branching (what most Rocket projects do):
  Developer pushes code → Netlify deploys → migrations run against PRODUCTION DB
  If migration fails: production is broken
  If migration has bad data: production data corrupted

With branching:
  Developer opens PR → Supabase creates isolated DB branch
  Netlify preview deploy connects to the branch DB
  Migrations tested on branch first
  On merge to main: migrations run against staging/production only after passing
```

---

## Setup: GitHub Integration

```
1. Dashboard → Project Settings → Integrations → GitHub
   → Connect repository
   → Enable "Create branches for pull requests"

2. Supabase creates a branch automatically when:
   - A PR is opened against main/master
   - Manual: supabase branches create --name feature/my-feature

3. Each branch gets:
   - Its own Postgres DB (isolated from production)
   - Its own API URL and keys (auto-generated)
   - Copied schema from main branch at creation time
   - Empty data (unless seed.sql is configured)
```

