## GitHub Actions — Migration CI/CD

```yaml
# .github/workflows/supabase-migrate.yml
name: Supabase Migrations

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
    paths: ['supabase/migrations/**']

jobs:
  migrate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Setup Supabase CLI
        uses: supabase/setup-cli@v1
        with:
          version: latest

      - name: Link to project
        run: supabase link --project-ref ${{ secrets.SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF }}
        env:
          SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN }}

      - name: Run migrations
        run: supabase db push --password ${{ secrets.SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD }}
        env:
          SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN }}
```

```bash
# Required GitHub secrets (set in repo Settings → Secrets):
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN   # from supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF    # your production project ref
SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD    # from Dashboard → Settings → Database → Database password
```

