## Seed Data Per Environment

```sql
-- supabase/seed.sql — runs after every db reset (local dev only)
-- For branch seeds, use supabase/seed.sql OR create branch-specific seeds

INSERT INTO public.profiles (id, full_name, email)
VALUES
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001', 'Test User',  'test@example.com'),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 'Admin User', 'admin@example.com');

INSERT INTO public.user_roles (user_id, role)
VALUES
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001', 'member'),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002', 'admin');
```

```bash
# Apply seed to a branch (creates test data without touching production)
supabase db reset --linked   # resets branch DB + applies seed.sql

# Branch management
supabase branches list
supabase branches create --name feature/add-teams
supabase branches delete feature/add-teams --confirm

# Get branch credentials (for manual wiring)
supabase branches get feature/add-teams
```

